                "ingredientId": "cmppmgyut0007i0v4w9b2nag0",
                "ingredientSlug": "stock-lamb"
              },
              {
                "name": "Red wine",
                "unit": "ml",
                "amount": 150,
                "prepNote": null,
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": true,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49fb2700e8rkv4d4sxs8mj",
                "ingredientSlug": "red-wine"
              }
            ],
            "defaultServings": 6
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Prepare and season",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Remove the lamb from the fridge one hour before cooking. Heat the oven to 140 degrees C fan.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Using a sharp knife, make deep slits all over the shoulder about 2 cm apart. Push a piece of garlic and rosemary into each slit.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Rub the joint all over with olive oil and scatter the salt generously over the top and sides.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Slow-roast",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Place the shoulder fat-side up in a roasting tin. Pour the stock and red wine (if using) around the base. Cover tightly with foil. ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Slow-roast",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpsohsur000034v48hvh5qjr"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " for 5 hours covered, then remove the foil and continue for 1 further hour until the skin is golden and the meat yields completely when pressed.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Transfer to a warm board and ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "rest",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpedfvv30001x4v4rzqb2aze"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " for 30 minutes under a tent of foil before serving.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Raise the temperature to 160 degrees C, reseal with foil, and cook for another hour. The joint needs to reach an internal temperature above 90 degrees C for collagen to convert.",
                "cause": "The oven temperature was too low, or the foil seal was loose and steam escaped.",
                "symptom": "Meat is still firm and not pulling apart after 6 hours"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add stock in the base from the start and ensure the foil is sealed tightly against the sides of the tin. Check at the 3-hour mark and top up if needed.",
                "cause": "Not enough liquid in the base, or the foil was too loose.",
                "symptom": "The base of the pan has caught and burnt"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Remove the foil completely for the last hour. Raise the oven to 180 degrees C fan if more colour is wanted.",
                "cause": "The uncovered hour was not long enough, or the oven was still covered.",
                "symptom": "Fat on top is still soft and pale, not golden"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Deglaze the tin with 200 ml of hot stock and stir up any sticky bits for a simple sauce.",
                "cause": "Foil was not sealed and steam escaped during the long cook.",
                "symptom": "The cooking juices have reduced to nothing"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Variations",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Stud with anchovy fillets alongside the garlic for a deeper savoury flavour without a fishy taste. Add whole peeled shallots to the base of the tin for the last 2 hours. A pomegranate molasses glaze brushed on in the final uncovered hour gives a Middle Eastern character.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Slow-roast lamb shoulder has roots across Mediterranean and Middle Eastern cooking. The British version settled into the Sunday lunch repertoire through the twentieth century. It is one of the few roasting joints that truly rewards neglect: the longer it cooks, within reason, the better it gets.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 6,
    "yieldDescription": null,
    "difficulty": "BEGINNER"
  },
